project.name: BJC.2x HW2 template
project.notes: This is the answer key for the BJC.2x Guess-a-Word game, part 2 project. The goal of this project is to provide students with the opportunity to use the higher-order function skills they've just learned by extending the Guess-a-word project from the first MOOClet. The template file contains five blocks with empty bodies that need to be filled in. The source code was written by Yifat Amir and polished by Dan Garcia. Creative Commons 4.0 BY-NC-SA

custom-block.comment: Returns a word randomly chosen from the first argument (list of words) that has length equal to the second argument (number).

Returns a word equal in length to the first (word) argument, but when the letter not in the second (list of letters) argument, it is replaced by a - (dash). display-pattern-of(bjc)with({c,q,x,b}) ==> b-c

Returns true if all the letters in the first (word) argument are in the second (list of letters) argument. player-won?-secret(bjc)guesses({j,c,e,b,r}) ==> true player-won?-secret(bjc)guesses({c,q,x,b}) ==> false
Returns the number of the first (letter) argument in the second (word) argument. number-of(s)in(scissors) ==> 4
